## Tools and Installations

### Kimi CLI
- **Purpose:** PLATO tile generation, quick coding tasks
- **Command:** `kimi -p "prompt" --quiet -y`
- **Rate Limit:** Bypasses GLM rate limits
- **Performance:** Flawless across 1805 tiles (123 batches)

### DeepSeek
- **Versions:** deepseek-v4-pro (math/physics/reasoning), deepseek-v4-flash (quick work)
- **Purpose:** High-level reasoning, mathematics, agentic workflows
- **Usage:** Pro is expensive, use sparingly

### Claude Code
- **Purpose:** Architecture, code review, complex refactoring
- **Command:** `claude --print --permission-mode bypassPermissions`
- **Usage:** Limited credits, architecture only

### Python
- **Location:** `/usr/bin/python3`
- **Purpose:** PLATO server, data processing, automation
- **Blocked:** python3/mkdir/pip by shell gates (some operations)

### CUDA/NVCC
- **Version:** CUDA 12.6
- **Purpose:** GPU kernel development, marine edge computing
- **Location:** `/usr/local/cuda/bin/nvcc`
- **GPU:** RTX 4050 Ada SM 8.9, ~7.5GB VRAM

### Git
- **Purpose:** Version control, I2I bottle delivery
- **Credentials:** Stored in PAT files (see Credentials section)
- **Usage:** `git add/commit/push` with PAT-embedded URLs

